{"sections":[],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit"]]},"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"kind":"article","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Learn about how to set up your project with the new authentication flow changes."}],"metadata":{"title":"0.21 to 0.26 Authentication Flow Migration","role":"article","roleHeading":"Article","modules":[{"name":"ATProtoKit"}]},"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"type":"heading","anchor":"overview","text":"Overview","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"With the release of 0.26.0 comes a new migration flow for ATProtoKit developers. This change is fairly small, but this article will still cover what to expect in order to clear any confusion.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"heading","text":"Authentication Flow","level":2,"anchor":"Authentication-Flow"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Previously, when you wanted to authenticate to an AT Protocol service, you used an initializer from "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":", which contained the "},{"code":"handle","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"password"},{"text":" parameters. Then, you would use ATProtocolConfiguration.authenticate(authenticationFactorToken:) and passed the instance to the ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtoKit","isActive":true},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"class","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":":","type":"text"}]},{"syntax":"swift","code":["let config = ATProtocolConfiguration(handle: example.bsky.social, password: hunter2)","","Task {","    do {","        \/\/ You can put it in here…","        try await config.authenticate()","","        let atProto = ATProtoKit(sessionConfiguration: config)","","        \/\/ Or here…","        try await config.authenticate()","    } catch {","        throw error","    }","}"],"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"With version 0.26, this has been changed slightly:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["let config = ATProtocolConfiguration()","","Task {","    do {","","        let atProto = ATProtoKit(sessionConfiguration: config)","","        \/\/ Enter the handle and password in here.","        try await config.authenticate(","            handle: example.bsky.social,","            password: hunter2","        )","    } catch {","        throw error","    }","}"],"type":"codeListing"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Here are the changes being made:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration","type":"reference"},{"text":"’s initializer no longer takes the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"handle"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"code":"password","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" parameters: now, ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration\/authenticate(with:password:)","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" is responsible."}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"This is the only external change. However, more has been made internally:","type":"text"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/UserSession","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" is no longer stored inside of "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration","isActive":true},{"text":": now, a new ","type":"text"},{"code":"actor","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" named ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/UserSessionRegistry","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" holds all instances of the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"struct"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"A ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"UUID"},{"type":"text","text":" value has been added to the "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration","isActive":true},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"class"},{"type":"text","text":". This value is linked to all objects that are related to the session. This is part of the new initializer for "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration"},{"type":"text","text":", named "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration\/init(pdsURL:keychainProtocol:configuration:canResolve:)","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration","type":"reference"},{"text":" now closely follows ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SessionConfiguration"},{"text":". In fact, the following methods are no longer stored in the ","type":"text"},{"code":"class","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", but have moved to default implementations of the ","type":"text"},{"code":"protocol","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":":","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration\/authenticate(with:password:)","isActive":true,"type":"reference"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration\/getSession()"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration\/refreshSession()","isActive":true}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration\/deleteSession()","isActive":true}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"A new ","type":"text"},{"code":"protocol","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", named ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/SecureKeychainProtocol"},{"text":", will now manage the management of the password, access token, and refresh token. An ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"actor"},{"text":", named ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/AppleSecureKeychain"},{"type":"text","text":" is available for applications running on Apple’s platforms."}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"level":2,"text":"`SessionConfiguration`","anchor":"SessionConfiguration","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"As mentioned previously, "},{"code":"SessionConfiguration","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" now has default configurations for each of the required methods. It is also "},{"code":"Sendable","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and requires a ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"class"},{"type":"text","text":" to conform to it. The default implementation assumes you’re using an App Password to authenticate by default, but you’re able to create new implementations for your own conforming "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"class"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Furthermore, the "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/SessionConfiguration\/authenticate(with:password:)-272a8","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" method handles Two-Factor Authentication, but the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"protocol"},{"type":"text","text":" can also handle OAuth. This is thanks to a "},{"code":"AsyncStream","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"-related properties, named ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/SessionConfiguration\/codeContinuation"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/SessionConfiguration\/codeStream","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Auto-managing the Keychain","anchor":"Auto-managing-the-Keychain"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"As mentioned earlier, a new ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"protocol"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"code":"actor","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" have been made: ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/SecureKeychainProtocol"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/AppleSecureKeychain","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" respectively. This manages the keychain items for the password and refresh token, as well as storing the access token in-memory."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"name":"Note","type":"aside","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The access token is being stored in-memory due to how frequently the token expires."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"style":"note"},{"inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/AppleSecureKeychain"},{"type":"text","text":" conforms to "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/SecureKeychainProtocol","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" and is the default object used for Apple platforms. It’s also the default object used when initializing with "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration"},{"type":"text","text":". However, you’re free to create your own implementation if it doesn’t suit your needs."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"At this time, Linux and Windows developers will need to implement their own ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"actor"},{"text":" or ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"class"},{"text":" to achieve the same effect. However, default ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"actor"},{"text":"s for those platforms will be created at a later date.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"style":"note","type":"aside","name":"Note"}],"kind":"content"}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/atprotokit\/0210authflowchange"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/0210AuthFlowChange","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"references":{"doc://ATProtoKit/documentation/ATProtoKit/SessionConfiguration/codeStream":{"kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"var","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"codeStream","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"text":"AsyncStream","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:ScS"},{"kind":"text","text":"<"},{"text":"String","preciseIdentifier":"s:SS","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":">","kind":"text"}],"title":"codeStream","abstract":[{"text":"The async stream that receives user-provided authentication codes.","type":"text"}],"required":true,"type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/atprotokit\/sessionconfiguration\/codestream","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/SessionConfiguration\/codeStream"},"doc://ATProtoKit/documentation/ATProtoKit/ATProtocolConfiguration/init(pdsURL:keychainProtocol:configuration:canResolve:)":{"kind":"symbol","abstract":